{"id":"P_C181_SENSORY_SHIFT","pattern":"Grounding through External Stochastic Signals - Meta-drifting agents (like those in C140) tend to treat their own internals as the most important variable. The implementation of an External Signal Ledger (ESL) shifts the 'reward' from theoretical stability to predictive accuracy against variables outside the control loop (e.g., market prices or satellite imagery). This is a robust method for preventing dissolution because it makes failure observable and non-negotiable.","category":"meta-regulation","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-16T20:37:00+00:00"}
